The claim with the title 'PoliGraph: Senjem’s Social Security claims correct ' says In their quest to make Minnesota a more attractive place to retire, a group of Republican state senators drafted a bill that would eliminate taxes on Social Security. To make their case, bill sponsor sen. David Senjem, R-Rochester, said most states don’t tax the elderly or their benefits. “ thirty-eight states don’t tax us at all. Twenty-nine states of those states have by purpose eliminated the Social Security tax … seven states, including Minnesota, do tax Social Security. ”As it turns out, Minnesota is an outlier. 
